<DOCNO>GH951117-000020</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951117-000020</DOCID>
<DATE>951117</DATE>
<HEADLINE>NEWS DIGEST</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339541</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Prisoner dies
A PRISONER was found dead in his cell at Perth's maximum security jail
yesterday morning. His name was being withheld until relatives are told.
Stress at work
MORE than 200 people working for Grampian Regional Council asked for
counselling because of stress problems at work last year.
-Woman named
A WOMAN whose body was found at the bottom of cliffs at Arbroath on Monday was
named yesterday as Mrs Agnes Yeaman, 65, a widow, of Cairnie Street, Arbroath.
Police said there were no suspicious circumstances.
Farmer fined
A FARMING company which broke regulations relating to BSE - mad cow disease -
was fined #500 at Perth yesterday. David Burnett and Sons, of Burridge Farm,
Newark, Nottinghamshire, admitted applying a false trade description to 14
cattle it supplied to Perth Fresh Meat Ltd.
Poppy record
THE Poppy Day appeal in Arbroath - population 23,000 - raised #10,595 - the
best per-head figure for any Scottish town this year.
</TEXT>
