<HEADLINE>Subsidies for bullfights stop</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339562</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MULTI-MILLION pound Euro-payments which subsidise Spanish bullfighting are to
end following an investigation by the Commission.
EU Agriculture Commissioner Franz Fischler has told Euro-MPs he has found a way
of cutting out payments for farmers fattening up cattle for the ring without
threatening grants to other types of bull-breeders.
For years, Brussels claimed it was difficult to prevent bull-breeding subsidies
- paid at age 10 months and again at 22 months - from going to breeders rearing
animals for the bullring. However, Mr Fischler's solution is simple - subsidies
will be paid only at slaughter in future.
About 900 Spanish ranchers who produce 30,000 bulls to be killed at fights were
pocketing subsidies designed to help prop up impoverished beef farmers.
</TEXT>
