<HEADLINE>Cycling silence</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339565</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Glasgow Cycling Campaign congratulates Edinburgh City Council on its
commitment to spend #300,000 on cycling facilities in its first year and notes,
with concern, the deafening silence enamating from George Square on the subject
of cycling and sustainable transport in Glasgow.
Glasgow City Council's recent decisions to press ahead with the M74 northern
extension and allow the construction of a new 2000-space multi-storey
city-centre car-park as part of the Buchanan Galleries are not part of a
sustainable transport policy.
Glasgow's miles better? Not if you are a cyclist.
Neil McDonald,
Vice-Convener, Glasgow Cycling Campaign,
53 Cochrane Street,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
