<HEADLINE>Briton tells of finding wife's body</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>13</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339598</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Nairobi, Thursday
THE anguished husband of a British woman killed and raped during a robbery at
their home in Kenya told a Nairobi judge today how he found her naked from
waist down in their baby's bedroom.
Adam Winter, 28, paused to fight back tears when prosecutor Horace Okumu asked
him to describe what he saw when he went into the room where his 31-year-old
wife Caron lay dead.
``She was lying on the floor and there was very much blood,'' Winter said.
``She was unclothed from the waist down. She was facing upward.''
He said he tried to revive her with mouth-to-mouth resuscitation, but gave up,
picked up the baby from the crib where he had placed her, and went outside.
Mrs Winter was raped and killed on July 31, 1994, during a midday robbery
staged by five or six men at the couple's home just 100yds from that of Kenya's
attorney-general.
Winter said the men were ransacking drawers in the living room and that his
15-month-old daughter was sitting on the floor, playing with the papers the men
were throwing around, when he walked in through the front door.
``One of the men ordered me to lie down, but before I could do so another one
of them hit me on the back of the head and I fell down,'' Winter told High
Court Judge Samuel Bosire.
He said he produced his wallet to hand over $350, but it was knocked out of his
hand.
``I pretended to be unconscious as they continued beating me and demanding
money,'' he said. ``They then left me alone, but I could hear their movements.
They took off my shoes.''
Yusuf Rashid Wamasoro, 22, James Washikoba, 26, both Ugandans, and Kenyan
Alexander Shikavale, 37, all deny murder. They face death by hanging if
convicted.
The hearing was adjourned until Tuesday.-AP
</TEXT>
