<TEXT>
Is end nigh for
St Michael?
MARKS &amp; Spencer yesterday played down talk that it was on the verge of ditching
its ``St Michael'' own brand.
The brand has existed since 1930 but a review of the business due to be
completed next June, could recommend that it be scrapped.
Overseas, M&amp;S is better known than its brand. However, the vast majority of the
group's business continues to be in the UK.
Airport order
ROTARY International of Newtownabbey, Co Antrim, has won a #5m order to provide
temporary lighting and power systems for the development of Chek Lap Kok
Airport in Hong Kong - Asia's biggest construction site.
Flower power
KEVIN Morley, chairman of the Birkdale Group, and Ian Steven, chairman and
managing director of Ann Street Brewery, have been appointed non-executive
directors of Flying Flowers.
Hammerson buys
HAMMERSON has exchanged contracts for the acquisition of Globe House in central
London for #18.25m from CIN Properties.
</TEXT>
