<DOCNO>GH951117-000110</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951117-000110</DOCID>
<DATE>951117</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Prescient poem</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339673</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
APOCALYPSE now! Bad enough that Bill Shackleton - who must have marvelled often
at the wonders of the universe - should be unwilling to accept that Amelia
Simonini does live in Flat 3 on the fourth floor of the tower block at 2
Calligarry, Sleat, Isle of Skye.
But to find on the same page William Hunter saying ``whoever wrote'' the Song
against Grocers, Chesterton's prescient warning of the perils awaiting a
country which might have as Prime Minister someone raised in the grocer's
philosophy!
The righteous minds of innkeepers
Induce them now and then
To crack a bottle with a friend
Or treat unmoneyed men.
But who hath seen the Grocer
Treat housemaids to his teas
Or crack a bottle of fish sauce
Or stand a man a cheese?
Eric Orr,
14 Netherhill Crescent,
Paisley.
</TEXT>
