<TEXT>
TWO letters from reverend gentlemen in The Herald on November 14 - one
wondering whether the Church of Scotland is being marginalised because a
Glasgow minister's knighthood went unreported, and the other attempting to poke
fun at another correspondent's name and address.
Obviously God's concern extends from the mighty to the humble.
Douglas Briggs,
Turakina,
Strathpeffer.
