<TEXT>
JOHN Foster (November 15) completely misses the point with regard to the
proposed launch of the Socialist Labour Party.
This party will have the potential to attract thousands of youth, animal
rightists, motorway protesters, nuclear disarmers, etc, who would have no truck
with Blairism. It would also have the potential to re-politicise many of my
(and John Foster's) generation who have become disillusioned and have dropped
out of politics.
Such developments would strengthen, not weaken, the positon of those who prefer
to remain within the (New) Labour Party and fight from within. Decades of
Stalinist dogmatism have blinded John Foster to this possibility.
Jimmy Johnston,
2 Balmore Place,
Glasgow.
