<TEXT>
Safety first: Stephanie Hopkins, of Glenrothes, celebrated her third birthday
yesterday by becoming the first member of the Children's Traffic Club.
Stephanie, who met Police Inspector Alan McIlvarie, was taken to Fife Police
Headquarters at Dysart, near Kirkcaldy, in a police traffic car, where she was
presented with a special birthday card and pack from the traffic club by the
force. Organisers estimate that half of all three-year-olds in Scotland will
join the club, giving an estimated membership of 30,000 in its first year.
