<HEADLINE>Fears grow for six on trawler</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339719</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FEARS were growing last night for an Irish fishing vessel missing with six men
on board.
A search involving three Nimrods from RAF Kinloss and several lifeboats was
called off last night and was resumed at first light this morning.
The 70ft Carrick Active, from Greencastle, had been fishing off Donegal when
she went missing. Coastguards did not pick up any distress signals.
The Irish authorities alerted Clyde coastguard at midnight on Wednesday and
yesterday the Nimrods were joined in a search of the gale-swept seas by four
helicopters and three lifeboats. A Royal Navy helicopter was on standby at
Prestwick.
</TEXT>
