ROUND-UP
GARY Armstrong has a busy weekend. Not only will he be standing by as a
replacement for Scotland in the international against Western Samoa at
Murrayfield but he will return for Jed-Forest for the important second division
premiership match against Selkirk at Riverside Park on Sunday.
Jed, who won by only 17-16 against Dundee in Armstrong's absence last week,
would be certain of promotion if they were to take even one point off Selkirk.
Armstrong missed the win at Mayfield as he was to lead Scotland A against the
Samoans the following day.
Boroughmuir, bidding to jump over Melrose to the top of the first division,
have recalled Alistair Cadzow for the match against Watsonians at Myreside on
Sunday. He takes over in the back row from Stuart Reid, who is to make his
international debut tomorrow.
Grant Blacklock will be Hawick's hooker in place of Jim Hay against Edinburgh
Academicals at Mansfield Park. Hay, like Reid, will be playing for Scotland for
the first time.
q GLASGOW Southern will honour three of their forwards - Alex McDougall, Stuart
Aitken, and Gavin Walsh - at a dinner at Braidholm on Monday.
McDougall will be playing his 500th first-team game when Southern seek to
secure promotion to the third division when they visit Kilmarnock on Sunday,
and Aitken will have his 100th match for the club six days later, when Ayr
visit Braidholm. That match next week also will be Walsh's last premier league
game for Southern before he departs for Bristol.
Southern have listed John Clinkenbeard in their squad for Bellsland in the hope
that he can return to the back row after a leg injury.
q THE first Scotland under-21 international against England will take place at
Gateshead on Tuesday, December 12. The match is part of a double-header before
the England A-Western Samoa game.
