<HEADLINE>Archibald back again</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>40</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975339761</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BASKETBALL
GREAT Britain and Scotland internationalist Bobby Archibald, who officially
retired at least for the third time at the end of last season, could be in the
frame for an appearance for Livingston Bulls in their first match of the season
with arch-rivals Edinburgh Burger Kings at Meadowbank tonight.
The 39-year-old former Paisley player could be the man to counter Kings'
leading scorer, Derek Frame.
Archibald helped Bulls to another cup and league double last season, then said:
``That's it, definitely no more.''
But, with fellow GB cap Iain Maclean unavailable, club secretary Archibald, a
6ft 6in centre, stepped in to help the team against Edzell two weeks ago, and
scored 10 points, though they went down to their first defeat for two years.
</TEXT>
